The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Amittrajit going for another podium
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: Calcuttas Amittrajit Ghosh will go for another podium finish when the fourth round of the seventh JK Tyre National Racing Championships in Sriperumbudur near Chennai Saturday and Sunday. The inaugural round of these championships was held in Calcutta, while the second and third rounds, presented by Maruti Suzuki, were held at the newly-built track in Coimbatore. At the end of round three Armaan Ebrahim leads the Formula LGB category with 47 points followed by Ameya Walavalkar and Rajyavardhan Vijayakumar with 30 and 29 points, respectively, according to information reaching here. Gaurav Gill leads the Formula Maruti category with 48 points. Rayomand Banajee in second position with 27 and Amittrajit third, also with 27, but having had less wins. In the Esteem Saloons JD Madan leads with 41 points, ahead of Radha Selvaraj (also 41).  Copyright 
